27,http://www.armslist.com/posts/1937027,"For Sale:  Coonan Arms .357 1911, 5"" slide 6"" barell 357","Virginia, Virginia, United States","$ 1,200","Listed On: Monday, July 29, 2013",Handguns,Colt                                                                                ,357 Magnum                                                                                ,Single Action                                                                                ,Revolver,"The Coonan .357 Magnum was modeled after the Colt 1911. Note the same clean lines, and functioning was flawless. Building a pistol to handle this hot revolver cartridge, Coonan guaranteed dependability by adopting the time-honored Colt Model 1911 design. The author firing the Coonan found the recoil dampened by shifting weight to the muzzle end of the weapon. fast recovery makes this pistol ideal for competition. Firing the Coonan. Distance about thirty yards, Target is a steel plate over 1/2"" thick. Author discovered .357 Magnum slammed plate off the top of the wood block, while .38 Special only gave them a good shove. Item is used but in great condition, looks to be unfired but not guaranteed."

29,http://www.armslist.com/posts/1937029,For Sale:  Preban Norinco,"Alabama, Alabama, United States","$ 1,800","Listed On: Monday, July 29, 2013",Rifles,Norinco                                                                                ,7.62x39                                                                                ,Semi-automatic                                                                                ,Rifle,"I have for sale a super nice and preban Norinco NMH 91 RPK battle rifle chambered in 7.62x39. The rifle is an early variant and has the true pistol grip, and not the sporterized stock. Please note, this is not just one of the Russian or Yougo or chinease sporterized RPK rifles which just have a longer barrel and bipod and pass for an RPK, just because they have bipod and RPK barrel. This is a true RPK with heavier components. This is also the only AK variant other than the true Dragunov rifles which is a Match grade file. The bipod swivels on the sides and also has extra long legs. The rifle has a very pleasant trigger and beautiful bluing and beautiful blonde wood furniture. If this rifle has been fired at all it has not been fired much as still looks very nice. The rifle also comes with the factory sling. If you are looking for a Preban RPK, this is as nice as they come, plus has the advantage of being a match grade rifle. Thank you for your time and consideration."

47,http://www.armslist.com/posts/1937047,For Sale:  Beretta Nano Carry Package,"Winder, Atlanta, Georgia",$ 675,"Listed On: Monday, July 29, 2013",Handguns,Beretta USA                                                                                ,9mm Luger (9x19)                                                                                ,Striker Fire                                                                                ,Pistol,"I am selling a Beretta Nano package. It has been carried for two months. Shows a little holster wear, but nothing major. About 200 - 300 rounds have been fired out of this little guy. There are some ""custom"" work done to it. The chassis and some internal parts have been polished to improve trigger pull. As you know, the trigger is double action. The polish job has made the trigger pull smoother, but I haven't felt a difference as far as weight goes. Also, Nano's do not have manual controls...therefore I have added a slide release (just a personal preference). The FDE frame has been modified to work with the slide release. The black and pink frames are stock but can be modded to work with the slide release. Also included is a spare, un-modded slide lock if you choose not to use the slide release.
Package includes:
Nano w/ 2 6rd mags, box, docs, lock...
1 additional 6rd mag (3 total)
1 8 rd mag
2 Pearce Pinky Extensions (made for Kahr K9/40 but fits the Nano mags)
Black Frame
Pink Frame (for the ladies...or those confident guys)
Un-modded Slide Lock
Lasermax Laser
Trijicon Night Sights
Little Foxx Holster made to fit the Nano w/ Lasermax attached (super comfortable incase you've never tried one...highly recommended)

This is the ultimate Nano carry package with all the bells and whistles and then some. Not looking for any trades, just ""thinning the herd"". Selling for $675. I would like to see your GA driver's license and GA weapons carry license.
Thanks for looking!"

317,http://www.armslist.com/posts/1937317,For Sale/Trade:  18 year olds in Tn,"Nashville, Nashville, Tennessee",$ 0,"Listed On: Monday, July 29, 2013",Handguns,no type,no type,no type,no type,"I do not understand how come all these people listing on this site are unaware of their own state laws.

In Tennessee, there are no waiting periods or any other BS besides a simple background check to buy a gun from a federally licensed dealer. You just walk into the store, pick out your gun, fill out simple paperwork and wait a few minutes for the background check, and walk out with your gun. Any gun store is a federally licensed dealer and you must be 21 to buy a handgun from them. 18 for a rifle or shotgun.

However, if you purchase your handgun from a gun show or from an ad in the classifieds section or used from an individual that is not a federally licensed dealer, the minimum age is 18 and there is no background check required. So basically 21 to buy from a licensed gun store, 18 to buy in a private exchange/sale.
Also, in Tennessee you must be must be 21 to apply for a Concealed firearms permit.
Have fun.
Source: tn.gov do some research for your own clarification."

835,http://www.armslist.com/posts/1937835,For Trade:  Rare Stainless .357 Desert Eagle,"Northeast, Tampa/St. Pete, Florida",Offer,"Listed On: Monday, July 29, 2013",Handguns,Magnum Research                                                                                ,357 Magnum                                                                                ,Single Action,no type,"Here's an interesting piece of Magnum Research history. This is a .357 Magnum Mark I pistol from 1985. It has a 6"" Magnaported barrel and Millet adjustable sights  (white outline rear and bright orange front). It comes with one stainless mag and one blued mag. Comes with the original box, literature, cleaning rod, brush and gas system scraping tool. The gun has a ""stainless' appearance and that's where the story gets interesting.

The Desert Eagle serial numbers began at ""3000."" The suffix ""S"" was used for ""stainless guns."" This pistol is serial 309x - S, making it one of the first 100 ""stainless"" Desert Eagles to ever be imported into this country. According to Magnum Research, these old guns that were catalogued as ""stainless"" were actually stainless steel cast frames along with Satin Nickel plated barrels and slides (made of chromoly steel). This one has black accents and it looks sharp. It handles screaming full-power .357 loads like a champ and recoils like a 9mm pistol. It's a ton of fun to shoot; nobody has shot it without having a huge smile on their face afterwards. Someone in the past 30 years ground down the sharp edge inside the trigger guard on the right side of the frame. If you're looking for a solid shooter that looks great, this is it!

It isn't very common to come across the ""stainless"" MKI in .357MAG, let alone one with the Millet sights and Magnaport factory upgrades. In fact, it was several years before I came across this one. I think it's safe to call it ""rare"" but this one is a shooting piece, not a collector's piece.
I don't want to sell it, but I would consider trades, plus or minus cash for:"
